# 04 — Multi-omics ablation: RNA + mutations + CNV + metabolomics

## Research question

Does adding more omics modalities (CNV, metabolomics) beyond RNA + mutations
improve drug-blind per-drug r?

## Background

The prior experiments (01–03) exhausted single-modality alternatives: RNA PCA
variants, foundation model embeddings, and RPPA proteomics all converge to the
same per-drug r. A multi-omics skeptic argues that the bottleneck is not any
single modality but information coverage: copy number variation (CNV) and
metabolomics capture orthogonal cell-state axes — gene amplification/deletion
and metabolic flux — absent from RNA+mutations. If the ceiling is an
information bottleneck rather than a fundamental limit, multi-omics integration
should push per-drug r higher.

## Experimental design

- **Model**: Ridge, 10-fold PASO drug-blind CV
- **Modalities**:
  - rna_mut: RNA PCA(550) + mutation PCA(200) (baseline, 750 dims)
  - rna_mut_cnv: + copy number variation (1050 dims)
  - rna_mut_metab: + metabolomics (975 dims)
  - rna_mut_all: + CNV + metabolomics (1275 dims)

