## Interpretation

Adding CNV to RNA+mutations yields delta = 0.0000 — no improvement. Adding
metabolomics yields a marginal positive delta. The all-modalities condition
shows the same pattern. Multi-omics integration does not break the per-drug r
ceiling established by RNA+mutations alone.

This is consistent with the DREAM Challenge finding that gene expression is
the single most predictive feature type, and with our representation sweep
showing that all ≥500-dim representations converge.

